<subSubSection id="C353655E69767A21DDA8284804F8FCC7" pageId="2" pageNumber="173" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BF636D569767A21DDA8284804F8FCC7" blockId="2.[163,1071,787,867]" pageId="2" pageNumber="173">
Comment: The known distribution of 
<taxonomicName id="4C494D5669767A21DF63284F07B9FC8C" baseAuthorityName="FAUVEL" baseAuthorityYear="1900" box="[616,753,787,809]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Rugilus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="173" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="longicollis">
<emphasis id="B93DEAC769767A21DF63284F07B9FC8C" box="[616,753,787,809]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="173">R. longicollis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
includes 
<collectingCountry id="F35E764569767A21DE5C284806E3FC8D" box="[855,939,787,809]" name="Georgia" pageId="2" pageNumber="173">Georgia</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry id="F35E764569767A21DEB328480162FC8D" box="[952,1066,787,809]" name="Azerbaijan" pageId="2" pageNumber="173">Azerbaijan</collectingCountry>
, and 
<collectingCountry id="F35E764569767A21DDC5286A05B1FCE2" box="[206,249,817,838]" name="Iran" pageId="2" pageNumber="173">Iran</collectingCountry>
, where the species is widespread and present also in the south. Its distribution is mapped in 
<bibRefCitation id="EFD84B2469767A21DC18281604E5FCC7" author="ASSING V" box="[275,429,845,867]" pageId="2" pageNumber="173" pagination="137 - 183" refId="ref11016" refString="ASSING V. (2011): On the Staphylinidae (Coleoptera) of Iran. II. New species and additional records, with special reference to the Paederinae, Xantholinini, and Aleocharinae. - Stuttgarter Beitrage zur Naturkunde Serie A, Neue Serie 4: 137 - 183." type="journal article" year="2011">ASSING (2011)</bibRefCitation>
.
</paragraph>
